HEADWORD: honey-eater
<hw>honey-eater</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>One of numerous species of small passerine birds of the family
<fam>Meliphagid⟦ae⟧</fam> having tongue and bill adapted for extracting
nectar, abundant in Australia and Oceania; -- called also
<altname>honeysucker</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> honeysucker.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>honey flower</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>honeyflower</ent>⟦br⟧
